Function Held in Cuba 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- A function for laying a floral basket before a portrait of President Kim Il Sung on a wall of the building of the Organization of Solidarity of the Peoples of Africa, Asia and Latin America
(OSPAAL) was held in Cuba on December 30 on the occasion of the New Year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials of the OSPAAL, the DPRK ambassador to Cuba and staff members of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants placed the floral basket before the portrait of the President and paid tribute to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Humberto Hernandez, secretary-general of the Executive Secretariat of the organization, addressing the function, expressed solidarity with the Korean people in their just struggle to smash the moves of the U.S. against the DPRK.

Results of S. Korean Authorities' Unreasonable Negotiations on Rice Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- The Democratic Workers' Party of south Korea vehemently condemned the results of the government's unreasonable negotiations on rice, according to south Korean MBC.
 It charged that the government decided to inform the World Trade Organization of the results of negotiations which calls on south Korea to increase the compulsory import of rice, terming this an act of deceiving peasants and yielding to other country's pressure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the "National Federation of Peasants Associations" held a press conference in front of the government building on December 30, demanding the authorities renegotiate the rice market opening. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the press conference speakers urged the authorities to renegotiate all issues, branding their rice negotiations as closed-door ones.

U.S. Scheme to Deploy New-type Missile Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of south Korea released a statement on Dec. 29 with regard to the sinister scheme of the United States to deploy in south Korea a new-type missile capable of penetrating underground for aggression on the north.
 The criminal aim of the U.S. in this is to destroy underground military facilities of the north by a preemptive strike and thereby neutralize its means of war deterrent and attain the goal of war against the north without difficulty, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This makes it all the clearer that the call for a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue and the resumption of the six-party talks made by the U.S. so often is no more than gimmicks intended to round off preparations for a war against the north pursuant to its robber-like doctrine of preemptive attack. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having deployed PAC-3 in Kwangju, south Korea, as a link in the whole chain of the aggressive missile defense system, the U.S. is now going to ship in the newly developed missile capable of destroying underground facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
This proves convincingly that it is now stepping into the last stage in its harebrained moves to start a war in Korea, come what may. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is going to throw the Korean nation into a terrible holocaust of nuclear war by deploying the new-type missile and starting a war against the north, no matter what the cost. The Koreans should thwart and frustrate the U.S. plan to deploy the new-type missile with close national cooperation.

Economic Policy for People Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification on December 29 reportedly published
a statement titled "Government, immediately enforce an economic policy for saving the people".
 It recalled that Kim Chun Bong, a worker of the Hanjin Heavy Industry, protested the government's suppression of labor with death at the dawn of December 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His death was a tragedy caused by the government's disregard of people's living and reforms, the desire of the people, and obviously murder, the statement said, and stressed: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government must resolutely break with the U.S. policy of "neo-liberalism" at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A shortcut to a stop to social catastrophe is for the government to be awakened and repeal part-time job system and enforce an economic policy for saving the people.

Do Not Dream of Unilateral "Disarmament": Rodong Sinmun 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- Ranking officials of the United States are vociferating about the need to "disarm" the DPRK by "collective pressure".
 Commenting on this, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Wednesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is nonsensical for the U.S. to urge the DPRK, which has been in hostile relationship and technically at war with it for over half a century, to accept the unilateral demand for "disarmament". The army and people of the DPRK will never lay down their arms unless the U.S. abandons its policy of aggression on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. "disarmament" doctrine is a sophism aimed to hamstring and destroy the armed forces of the DPRK. And it is a war doctrine intended to make a surprise preemptive attack on the DPRK after gaining the military upperhand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is not the slightest change in the basic stand of the United States not to co-exist with the DPRK. The U.S. seeks to disarm the DPRK ideologically, morally and militarily and then swallow it up as it did Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The DPRK has no alternate but to answer this strong-arm policy of the U.S. with increased self-defense capabilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-defense capabilities are the life and soul of the DPRK and attaching importance to arms is the core of its Songun policy. Apart from arms, is it impossible to think of the nation's sovereignty, right to existence and dignity. The DPRK will give full play to the might of its self-defense capabilities under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should never dream of the DPRK's unilateral "disarmament".

Japan Democratic Party's Anti-DPRK Racket under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- The Japan Democratic Party on Nov. 25 last year held a meeting of the headquarters for the settlement of the abduction
issue of the party at which it decided to introduce to the Diet session slated to take place this month a "bill on north Korean human rights" of Japanese brand urging the DPRK to improve its human rights performance.
 Minju Joson Wednesday in a signed commentary says the Japanese ultra-right reactionary forces' intention to adopt a law of the same nature as that of "the North Korean Human Rights Act" in the U.S. is little short of a declaration of a war as they reveal an intention to take direct part in implementing the U.S. policy of confrontation with the DPRK and thus play a part in overturning the system in it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those reactionary forces are persisting in their moves to stifle the DPRK, raising a hue and cry over the abduction issue though it had been already settled through the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration. Why? Through this they seek to bring down the system in the DPRK in collusion with the U.S. and evade the responsibility for compensating for the crimes committed by Japan in the past come what may, instead of redeeming them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another aim sought by them is to dramatize the abduction issue in a bid to stir up people's sentiment and use it for improving their image and thus create conditions favorable for grabbing power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They try to do harm to the dignified and strong socialist system of the DPRK. This is as foolish an act as trying to sweep the sea with a broom. 
 The DPRK is following Japan's every move with a high degree of vigilance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK re-clarifies its stand that if Japan finally opts for an all-out showdown with the DPRK, it has no alternative but to take a corresponding physical counter-action.
 The Japanese ultra-right reactionaries are well advised to behave themselves, mindful of the serious political and physical consequences to be entailed by their reckless anti-DPRK racket.

White-bellied Black Woodpeckers Grow in Number 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- The number of white-bellied black woodpecker has increased in the Mt. Myolak area, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The bird, found out in Kyonggi province for the first time in the summer of 1886, had inhabited in the area south of Mt. Songak and Mt. Chonma in Kaesong, Korea and in Tsushima, Japan. But the environmental deterioration and random fowling compelled it to disappear in Japan from October 1920. And it was hard to see the bird even in Korea.
 The DPRK government took a step to protect and propagate the bird in Juche 41 (1952) during the hard-fought Korean War, and designated the bird found in Mt. Songak as a natural treasure in 1956. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In September 1969 the DPRK Cabinet issued an ordinance on protecting and propagating white-bellied black woodpecker and the areas of Phyongsan and Rinsan Counties in North Hwanghae Province and Pongchon County in South Hwanghae Province were designated as reserves for the bird. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This made it possible to increase the number of the bird, which had been once on the brink of extinction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been living in the Mt. Myolak and Singye areas in North Hwanghae Province far north of the original habitat.

DPRK in General Onward March
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 5 (KCNA) -- The people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have turned out as one in the general onward march to mark
the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and national liberation as victors of the Songun revolution this year.
 The agricultural sector, the main front of socialist economic construction this year, takes the lead in the general onward march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the Ministry of Agriculture have set right soil for right crops and secured seeds of high-yielding varieties which require less amount of fertilizers and are resistant to  drought, blight and harmful insects in close contact with  provincial, city and county officials concerned. And they have worked out a bold plan to more than double the bean cultivation acreage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They, with detailed measures to do potato, bean and two-crop farming, are striving hard to increase quality organic fertilizer and bio-compost and to raise the level of mechanized work in farming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The farmers are all out in the preparation for farming and the entire Party, whole country and all the people are powerfully assisting the socialist countryside. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The workers of the Musan Mining Complex successfully carried out the blasting for blowing 150,000 ton earth on the New Year's Day to open a broad vista for increased iron ore production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songjin Steel Complex on the first day of the year produced iron and steel 1.5 times the daily result in the end of the previous year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Signal successes have been reported from power producers across the country including the Pukchang Thermal-power Complex and the Pyongyang Thermal-power Complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scientists of the Hamhung Branch under the Academy of Sciences are making redoubled efforts to solve scientific and technical issues arising in building a carbonate soda production process with a capacity of tens of thousands of tons, a process producing salt in an industrial way and a process of manufacturing catalytic agent pushing ahead with a drive to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The servicepersons are full of firm determination to discharge their mission and role as the standard-bearers of the Songun revolution.
